    "title": "Onion gravy",
    "subtitle": "Slow-caramelised onions, the sausage-and-mash companion",
    "excerpt": "A deep, sticky gravy built on slowly caramelised onions, beef stock, and a splash of stout. The classic companion for sausages, mash, and roast meats.",
    "sourceNotes": "Mrs Beeton, Book of Household Management (1861), Project Gutenberg #10136. Onion sauce entries.\n\nEliza Acton, Modern Cookery for Private Families (1845), Project Gutenberg. Brown sauces and gravies.",
    "body": {
      "type": "doc",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Onion gravy takes time but not skill. The onions need 30 to 40 minutes over low heat to properly caramelise, and there is no shortcut that replicates the depth of flavour that slow cooking builds. A wider, heavier pan makes the job faster and more even.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
